<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id79c374ae-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s3710"><num value="3710">§ 3710.</num><heading> Limitation on authority</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter authorizes the Foundation to perform any function the exclusive authority for which is provided to the National Park Foundation by subchapter II of chapter 1011 of title 54.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id79c374af-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/244/s11">Pub. L. 98–244, § 11</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/106/408/tII/s208">Pub. L. 106–408, title II, § 208</ref>, <date date="2000-11-01">Nov. 1, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/1781">114 Stat. 1781</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/113/287/s5/d/35">Pub. L. 113–287, § 5(d)(35)</ref>, <date date="2014-12-19">Dec. 19, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/3267">128 Stat. 3267</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/116/188/tI/s107/d">Pub. L. 116–188, title I, § 107(d)</ref>, <date date="2020-10-30">Oct. 30, 2020</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/134/920">134 Stat. 920</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id79c374b0-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id79c374b1-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id79c374b2-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2020—<ref href="/us/pl/116/188">Pub. L. 116–188</ref> inserted “exclusive” before “authority”.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2014—<ref href="/us/pl/113/287">Pub. L. 113–287</ref> substituted “subchapter II of chapter 1011 of title 54” for “<ref href="/us/pl/90/209">Public Law 90–209</ref> (<ref href="/us/usc/t16/s19e">16 U.S.C. 19e</ref> et seq.)”.</p>
</note>
